	pages = {1--4},
	annote = {Linare’s et al. present a DSE of security for memory-related exploits. The DSE explores the use of 24 different protections against memory-based attacks and its constraints are runtime, memory, and process cost. The tool then considers dozens of attacks and 2{\textasciicircum}24 versions of the user’s system are explored for their security against the attacks.

This paper presents a DSE of 
